{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:29:44.924309+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f537ad1f72c8b11348fa3ef459bb977dbcbe1319)", "id": "lc_c7ca9b95-cacb-4f0c-8a39-6005ecd9ec8a"}, {"type": "text", "text": "'use strict'\nconst path = require('path')\nconst defaultSettings = require('./src/settings.js')\nconst AutoImport = require('unplugin-auto-import/webpack')\nconst Components = require('unplugin-vue-components/webpack')\nconst { ElementPlusResolver } = require('unplugin-vue-components/resolvers')\nfunction resolve(dir) {\n  return path.join(__dirname, dir)\n}\n\nconst name = defaultSettings.title || 'vue Admin Template' // page title\n\n// If your port is set to 80,\n// use administrator privileges to execute the command line.\n// For example, Mac: sudo npm run\n// You can change the port by the following methods:\n// port = 9528 npm run dev OR npm run dev --port = 9528\nconst port = process.env.port || process.env.npm_config_port || 9528 // dev port\nconst isDev = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'\n// All configuration item explanations can be find in https://cli.vuejs.org/config/\nmodule.exports = {\n  /**\n   * You will need to set publicPath if you plan to deploy your site under a sub path,\n   * for example GitHub Pages. If you plan to deploy your site to https://foo.github.io/bar/,\n   * then publicPath should be set to \"/bar/\".\n   * In most cases please use '/' !!!\n   * Detail: https://cli.vuejs.org/config/#publicpath\n   */\n  publicPath: isDev ? '/' : '/vue3-admin-template/',\n  outputDir: 'dist',\n  assetsDir: 'static',\n  lintOnSave: isDev,\n  productionSourceMap: true,\n  css: {\n    sourceMap: isDev,\n  },\n  devServer: {\n    port: port,\n    open: false,\n    overlay: {\n      warnings: false,\n      errors: true,\n    },\n    before: require('./mock/mock-server.js'),\n  },\n  configureWebpack: {\n    // provide the app's title in webpack's name field, so that\n    // it can be accessed in index.html to inject the correct title.\n    name: name,\n    resolve: {\n      alias: {\n        '@': resolve('src'),\n      },\n    },\n    plugins: [\n      AutoImport({\n        resolvers: [\n          ElementPlusResolver({\n            importStyle: false,\n          }),\n        ],\n      }),\n      Components({\n        resolvers: [ElementPlusResolver()],\n      }),\n    ],\n  },\n  chainWebpack(config) {\n    // it can improve the speed of the first screen, it is recommended to turn on preload\n    config.plugin('preload').tap(() => [\n      {\n        rel: 'preload',\n        // to ignore runtime.js\n        // https://github.com/vuejs/vue-cli/blob/dev/packages/@vue/cli-service/lib/config/app.js#L171\n        fileBlacklist: [/\\.map$/, /hot-update\\.js$/, /runtime\\..*\\.js$/],\n        include: 'initial',\n      },\n    ])\n\n    // when there are many pages, it will cause too many meaningless requests\n    config.plugins.delete('prefetch')\n\n    // set svg-sprite-loader\n    config.module.rule('svg').exclude.add(resolve('src/icons')).end()\n    config.module\n      .rule('icons')\n      .test(/\\.svg$/)\n      .include.add(resolve('src/icons'))\n      .end()\n      .use('svg-sprite-loader')\n      .loader('svg-sprite-loader')\n      .options({\n        symbolId: 'icon-[name]',\n      })\n      .end()\n\n    config.when(process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'development', (config) => {\n      config\n        .plugin('ScriptExtHtmlWebpackPlugin')\n        .after('html')\n        .use('script-ext-html-webpack-plugin', [\n          {\n            // `runtime` must same as runtimeChunk name. default is `runtime`\n            inline: /runtime\\..*\\.js$/,\n          },\n        ])\n        .end()\n      config.optimization.splitChunks({\n        chunks: 'all',\n        cacheGroups: {\n          libs: {\n            name: 'chunk-libs',\n            test: /[\\\\/]node_modules[\\\\/]/,\n            priority: 10,\n            chunks: 'initial', // only package third parties that are initially dependent\n          },\n          elementUI: {\n            name: 'chunk-elementPlus', // split elementUI into a single package\n            priority: 20, // the weight needs to be larger than libs and app or it will be packaged into libs or app\n            test: /[\\\\/]node_modules[\\\\/]_?element-plus(.*)|[\\\\/]node_modules[\\\\/]_?@element-plus(.*)/, // in order to adapt to cnpm\n          },\n          commons: {\n            name: 'chunk-commons',\n            test: resolve('src/components'), // can customize your rules\n            minChunks: 3, //  minimum common number\n            priority: 5,\n            reuseExistingChunk: true,\n          },\n        },\n      })\n      // https:// webpack.js.org/configuration/optimization/#optimizationruntimechunk\n      config.optimization.runtimeChunk('single')\n    })\n  },\n}\n", "id": "lc_fd485793-30fe-4937-b668-f49e7e23992d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f38f7f5d-e6da-4073-81bb-69799af02f6c", "tool_call_id": "call_d191382c6bf543e5a14e5761", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:29:57.955698+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here is a complete description based on what the repository contains.\n\n---\n\n## How the template switches between development and production API base paths\n\nThe switching is driven by **Vue CLI's `.env` file mechanism** combined with per-mode environment files:\n\n| File | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` value | Used when |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.development` | `/dev-api` | `npm run dev` (default mode = `development`) |\n| `.env.production` | `/prod-api` | `npm run build` (default mode = `production`) |\n| `.env.staging` | `/stage-api` | `npm run build --mode staging` |\n\n**How it works:**\n\n1. **Environment files define the base URL.** Each `.env.*` file sets `VUE_APP_BASE_API` to a different prefix (`/dev-api`, `/prod-api`, or `/stage-api`). Vue CLI automatically loads the file matching the current `--mode`.\n\n2. **`vue.config.js` reacts to the mode.** The config reads `process.env.NODE_ENV` to set mode-dependent options (e.g., `publicPath`, source maps, lint-on-save, code splitting). It does **not** reference `VUE_APP_BASE_API` directly—it is embedded into the client bundle by Vue CLI's `dotenv` integration so that application code (e.g., Axios interceptors in `src/`) can read `process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API` at runtime.\n\n3. **Mock server is development-only.** In `vue.config.js`:\n   ```js\n   devServer: {\n     before: require('./mock/mock-server.js'),\n   }\n   ```\n   The `devServer.before` hook only runs during `npm run dev`, so mock API responses (including the login mock) only intercept requests in development. In production the app hits the real `/prod-api` backend.\n\n4. **Build-time optimization for production.** When `NODE_ENV !== 'development'`, `chainWebpack` adds `ScriptExtHtmlWebpackPlugin`, aggressive `splitChunks`, and a single `runtimeChunk`—none of which affect the API path, but they confirm the mode-based branching pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Mock login usernames and their tokens\n\nFrom **`mock/user.js`**, the `tokens` map defines two users:\n\n| Username | Token | Roles | Display Name |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **`admin`** | `admin-token` | `['admin']` | Super Admin |\n| **`editor`** | `editor-token` | `['editor']` | Normal Editor |\n\nThe mock login endpoint is:\n\n```\nPOST /vue-admin-template/user/login\n```\n\nIt reads `config.body.username`, looks it up in the `tokens` object, and returns:\n- **Success:** `{ code: 20000, data: { token: 'admin-token' } }` (or `'editor-token'`)\n- **Failure (unknown username):** `{ code: 60204, message: 'Account and password are incorrect.' }`\n\nA subsequent `GET /vue-admin-template/user/info` call takes the token as a query parameter and returns the corresponding user details (roles, introduction, avatar, name) from the `users` map. If the token is unrecognized it returns `{ code: 50008, message: 'Login failed, unable to get user details.' }`.\n\n---\n\n**In short:** the base API path is switched by swapping `.env.*` files via Vue CLI modes (`/dev-api` in dev, `/prod-api` in production, `/stage-api` in staging), and the two mock login accounts are `admin` (token `admin-token`) and `editor` (token `editor-token`).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1152, "prompt_tokens": 7878, "total_tokens": 9030, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 368, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6656, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005122768, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001897168, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00032256}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871385-CZf96UKO9r18pwWD48Fx", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea434-cf5c-7372-a58b-195e7cbce2ae-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7878, "output_tokens": 1152, "total_tokens": 9030, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6656}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 368}}}}]}}}
